<center><h1>Translation of Sigma Query</h1></center>

<IMG ALT=o SRC="fig7.gif" align=right width=200>

<h2>
The query in mathematical notation is:

S<sub>t</sub>(*)
(S<sub>x,y;v<sub>1</sub></sub>(*) world-map)
</h2><h3>
where v<sub>1</sub>=
x1 < x  < x2 & y1 < y < y2 & course-title = "visual languages"
</h3><h2>
In SQL-like language the query is:</h2><b>
<pre>
SELECT     t
CLUSTER    *
FROM       SELECT x,y
           CLUSTER *
           FROM world-map
           WHERE x1 < x  < x2 and
                 y1 < y < y2  and
                 course-title = "visual languages"
</pre>
